# Rust backend

Follow [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) and [backend/AGENTS.md](../backend/AGENTS.md). Do not assume — stop and ask the user if unsure. Update agent docs in the same change when backend conventions or workflows change.

## Layers

- `domain/` — no `application` or `infrastructure` imports
- `application/` — no `infrastructure` imports
- `infrastructure/` — handlers, Diesel, adapters; wire use cases here

## Handlers

- Match `infrastructure/document/` patterns: router → handler → `DocumentUseCases` / app state
- Multipart document create: `json` part + `file` part (see development_faq)

## Tests

- Unit tests: `Given*` setup structs, scenario-style names, `// Given` / `// When` / `// Then`
- Integration: `backend/tests/`, use `serial_test` when sharing Docker/state
- Never run `diesel migration run`; authoring `migrations/*.sql` is OK

